Welcome to Todos Santos!









Thank you for joining us for our workshop on wet-lab techniques in next-generation sequencing. Here is a summary of the topics that we are looking forward to covering.

Monday November 18

  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch (optional upon request with additional cost)
  • 13:00-13:30 Introduction to Todos Santos and Group Discussion
  • 13:30-14:30 Illumina sequencing chemistry and adapters
  • 14:30-15:30 DNA/RNA quality control: methods for estimation of nucleic acid concentration, purity and integrity
  • 15:30-15:45 Introduction to 16S rRNA microbiome profiling
  • 15:45-17:00 Wet-lab: Illumina 16S rRNA amplicon library construction
  • 17:00-18:00 Evening reception
  • 18:00-21:00 Dinner on your own

Tuesday November 19

  • 07:00-07:45 Breakfast
  • 08:00-08:30 Illumina Library quality control: Quantification
  • 08:30-09:00 Illumina Library quality control: Size selection
  • 09:00-10:30 Wet Lab: Magnetic bead cleanup and Illumina 16S amplicon library gel electrophoresis
  • 10:30-11:00 Barcoding and multiplexing techniques
  • 11:00-12:00 Fragmentation
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch
  • 13:00-14:00 Introduction to long-read DNA sequencing technologies
  • 14:00-16:30 Wet-lab: Construction of Oxford Nanopore libraries and sequencing on a MinIon
  • 16:30-18:00 Excursion: Sea turtle release at the beach!
  • 18:00-21:00 Dinner on your own

Wednesday November 20

  • 07:00-07:45 Breakfast
  • 08:00-08:30 Results from Oxford Nanopore sequencing run
  • 08:30-09:00 Making choices in high-throughput sequencing projects
  • 09:00-10:00 Introduction to RNA-seq methods
  • 10:00-11:00 Experimental design in high-throughput sequencing projects
  • 11:00-12:00 Flexible discussion time (UMIs, enrichment techniques, personal projects)
  • 12:00-13:00 Lunch (optional upon request with additional cost)
